# Phase 12: Cinematic Immersion & Ambient Glow

Creating a perfectly seamless transition between video content and the platform UI, inspired by YouTube's high-fidelity "Ambient Mode."

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Ambient Mode Logic**: We will use a low-resolution canvas behind the video player to sample colors in real-time. This can be toggled via the settings menu.

## Proposed Changes

### UI: Ambient Halo Engine
#### [MODIFY] [VideoPlayer.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx)
- **Canvas Backdrop**: Add a hidden canvas that samples video frames at 2 FPS (for efficiency).
- **CSS Blur Overlay**: Apply `backdrop-filter` and `blur(100px)` to the sampled image to create a soft, glowing halo.
- **Seamless Container**: Remove harsh borders and ensure the video player feels "embedded" in the glowing atmosphere.

---

### UX: Modern Playback Controls
#### [MODIFY] [VideoPlayer.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx)
- **Settings Toggle**: Add an "Ambient Mode" toggle in the gear menu.
- **Adaptive Gradient**: Ensure the control bar gradient doesn't clash with the ambient glow.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Check canvas sampling interval and performance impacts.

### Manual Verification
- Verify the "Glow" matches the dominant colors of the video.
- Confirm "Theater Mode" + "Ambient Mode" creates a seamless IMAX-like experience.
- Test toggle functionality in the settings menu.
